metadata.description:
Segment 336 in the Educational Broadcast Cable Series: " From the Ground Up " - Creating Energy Self-reliant, Environmentally Friendly, Homes and Systems, Produced and Directed by Tamara Lynn Scott, features Bob Dunn of Bonni Doon demonstrating the AC side of an off-the-grid, solar photovoltaic system hook up in which a Xantrex 48 volt inverter is used.
 This short cut is the opening musical theme of the series, " Freedom " , original composition, music, vocals of Tamara Lynn Scott, with short visual cuts of the subject matter to be covered in the thirty minute segment, namely hooking up protective the AC side of a Xantrex 48 volt inverter, discussing breaker switches, grounding, and wiring for the Xantrex inverter.
You may obtain the full thirty minute broadcast segment from the Producer at TLS.FromTheGroundUp@gmail.com.
These programs may be freely aired nationwide on all not-for-profit, educational ,Broadcast Cable Stations by obtaining a Broadcast Copy of the program.
These programs derive all their support from you, the viewing public.
Please consider supporting them through Paypal account TamaraLynnScott@gmail.com, or through ordering a DVD copy.
You may find more information on this series at http://TLS-FromTheGroundUp.blogspot.com
and other production segments at
http://TamaraLynnScottBroadcasts.blogspot.com.

This is the opening musical theme for the series, " Freedome ", the original music, vocals, composition of Tamara Lynn Scott, with short cuts of the visuals from the segment as overview. 
DVD copies of the complete thirty minute broadcast may be obtained through the Producer, Scott Com, at TLS.FromTheGroundUp@gmail.com.
